How to Run the application?

In working folder “my-app”, 
1. Input data to test_data.csv
2. execute command  —————————— “mvn package -e” to build the project
3. Execute command  —————————— “java -cp target/eroad-1.0-jar-with-dependencies.jar com.code_test.App“ to run the application
4. Verify result in test_output.csv

Assumptions and Regulations

1. Information (timezone and date time) from API are always valid

2. Due to the usage constraint from the free web service API, it will throw exception “daily limit of credits exceeded” when reached the daily quota (1000 calls).
Reference 
i. https://www.geonames.org/export/
ii. http://www.geonames.org/export/webservice-exception.html

3. The program will run properly only if 
a. Date time information provided in CSV with valid format “yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss”
b. Valid latitude, between -90 - +90
c. Valid longitude, between -180 - +180
d. Internet connection available, able to connect to the web service API, you can test the API - 
http://api.geonames.org/timezoneJSON?formatted=true&lat=-89.999921&lng=10.2&username=ajohnny&style=full
e. That location got timezone, some location like “lat -74.490947, long 171.220966” and “lat -54.490947, long 171.220966” do not have timezone name

3. Conversion of local time
a. If timezone name available for that location, will refer to the timezone name. If timezone name is not available for that location, will refer to the raw offset provided by the web service API

